Name: Connect/Additional-Resources
skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><panelset type="vertical"><panels><panel width="225"><components><template multiple="true" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><p>Some key systems and resources for partners are listed below. Get acquainted with these sites to take full advantage of your Informatica partnership.</p></br></contents><renderconditions logictype="and"/></template><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><a href="https://informatica.csod.com/LMS/catalog/Welcome.aspx?tab_id=-1" target="_blank"><h4>INFORM Learning</h4></a>
The INFORM learning management system will allow you to
manage Informatica coursework.<ul>
<li>Browse and search our directory of classes</li>
<li>Track your progress on classes and view your transcript</li></ul>
</br>
<a href="http://cloudacademy.informatica.com/" target="_blank"><h4>Informatica Cloud Academy</h4> </a>
Cloud Academy gives you access to training and certification, as
well as enablement resources - everything on Cloud.
<ul><li>Take advantage of complimentary partner training on
Informatica Cloud and a variety of Cloud integration areas</li></ul>
</br>
<a href="https://mysupport.informatica.com/login/login.html" target="_blank"><h4>MySupport</h4> </a>
MySupport furnishes help regarding Informatica solutions to
partners and customers. 
<ul><li>Request technical support</li>
<li>Access technical documentation</li></ul>
</br>
<a href="https://community.informatica.com/community/marketplace/" target="_blank"><h4>Informatica Marketplace</h4> </a>
Informatica Marketplace is a center for software vendors, system
integrators, and solution providers to list, browse, and purchase
applications and services for and with Informatica products. <ul>
<li>List your solutions and/or services to gain greater market
exposure</li>
<li>Review other Informatica solutions in the market</li></ul>
</br>
<a href="https://community.informatica.com/" target="_blank"><h4>Informatica Communities</h4> </a>
Informatica Communities are groups for discussion, organized
by various interests, including products, events, or expertise. <ul>
<li>Participate in discussions about products, training, and events</li>
<li>Engage with other Informatica users and experts</li></ul>
</br></contents></template></components></panel><panel><components/></panel></panels></panelset></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url=""/></css></resources></skuidpage>

@font-face {
    font-family: FuturaPTB;
    src: url(/resource/PARC_fonts/FuturaStd-Book.otf);
}

@font-face {
    font-family: ArialPARC;
    src: url(/resource/PARC_fonts/Arial.ttf);
}

/* General Styling */

.nx-page .ui-widget, body .nx-page, .nx-page td {
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Page Titles */

.nx-pagetitle-maintitle .ui-widget {
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Buttons */

.nx-actionbutton {
    float: left;
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    -webkit-border-radius: 3px;
    -moz-border-radius: 3px;
}

.ui-button, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default{
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: white;
    font-size: 12pt !important;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
}
.ui-button .ui-button-text{
    line-height: 41px;
}
.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-button-text{
    padding-left: 23px;
}

.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-icon{
    margin-top: -8px;
}

.ui-button.ui-state-hover, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default:hover{
    color: black;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary{
    color: #254EA2;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary.ui-state-hover{
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
    color: #254EA2;
    background: #eee;
}

.nx-actionselect {
    background: #254EA2;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: #FFF;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    line-height: 41px;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
    border-bottom: none;
}

.nx-actionselect.nx-conditiontoken:hover{
    background: #FFD400;
    color: black;
}

.nx-actionselect:hover, .nx-actionbutton:hover {
    color: #000;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.nx-actionselect.unavailable:hover, .nx-actionbutton.unavailable:hover {
    color: white;
    background: #ddd;
    cursor: default;
}

/* Dropdown */
.nx-actionselect-dropdown{
  background: none;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item {
  background: #254EA2;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #446AB8;
  color: white;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
  opacity: 1;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:first-child {
  border-top-right-radius: 3px;
  border-top-left-radius: 3px;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:last-child {
  border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom: none;
}


/* Tables */

table.nx-skootable-data {
    border-collapse:separate;
}

table.nx-skootable-data th {
    background: #939598;
    height:45px;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: lighter;
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    text-align:left;
    padding-left:10px;
    padding-right:10px;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody td, table.nx-skootable-data thead td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid white;
    height: 45px;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    background: #F0F0F0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

table.nx-skootable-data a {
    font-size: 13pt;
    color:#254EA2;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr td:nth-child(odd) {
    background-color:#F9F9F9
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr:nth-child(odd) td:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #F0F0F0;
}

table.nx-skootable-data .nx-skootable-order-icon{
    margin-top: 3px;
    background: url(data:image/png;base64,);
    width: 13px;
}
table .nx-skootable-order-number{
    display: none !important;
}

.nx-list-footer select {
    width:auto;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

.nx-list-footer {
    background:transparent;
}

.nx-list-footer .ui-button.ui-state-hover {
    background:#254EA2;
    color:white;
}
/* Table Search */

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox {
  width: 180px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  border: 1px solid #aaa;
  margin: 0 0 7px;
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
  line-height: 41px;
  height: 50px;
  background: #f5f5f5;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:disabled {
    background: #ddd;
    opacity: .6;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox::-webkit-input-placeholder {
   font-size: 12pt;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-moz-placeholder { /* Firefox 18- */
   font-size: 12pt; 
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox::-moz-placeholder {  /* Firefox 19+ */
   font-size: 12pt;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-ms-input-placeholder {  
   font-size: 12pt;
}

/* Field Editors */

.nx-basicfieldeditor-section-header {
  padding: 8px;
  border-bottom: none;
  font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16pt;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: #939598;
}

/* Tabs */
.ui-tabs{
    background: none;
}
.ui-tabs-nav{
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
}
.nx-lefttabs>.ui-tabs-nav li a{
    font-size: 12pt;    
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav .ui-tabs-anchor{
    width: 100%;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active, .ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active.ui-state-hover{
    background: #FFD400;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active a, .ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active.ui-state-hover a{
    color: black;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li{
    background: #254EA2;
    border-right:none;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-state-hover{
    background: #2A58B8;
}

.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:first-child{
    border-top-left-radius: 3px;
    border-top-right-radius: 3px;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:last-child{
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
}
.new-registration.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:nth-last-child(2){
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
}
/* Forms */
.nx-basicfieldeditor-item-label.nx-layout-above{
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #939598;
    line-height: 22pt;
    font-weight: 400;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-columngroup {
    background: none;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor{
    background: none;
    padding: 10px;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-section{
    background: none;
    margin: 10px;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-item{
    border-bottom: none;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor .nx-field input:not([type]){
    height: 25px;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}
.nx-editor .nx-basicfieldeditor-item select{
    max-width: none;
    height: 26px;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}
.nx-field input, .nx-field textarea, .nx-field select{
    background: white;
    border-color: #ddd;
    border-radius: 3px;
}

/* Wizard */
.nx-wizard .nx-editor-header-title{
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Multiselect */
.ui-multiselect-checkboxes label input{
    display: inline-block;
    position: relative;
    top: 3px;
}

button.ui-multiselect.ui-widget.ui-state-default {
  background: #254EA2;
  color: white;
  border-radius: 3px;
  border: none;
  min-height: 50px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  line-height: 41px;
}

button.ui-multiselect.ui-state-default:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
}

.ui-multiselect-header.ui-widget-header{
    background: #254EA2;
    font-size: 13pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    border: none;
    padding: 8px 3px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header ul li:nth-child(1) {
  margin-left: 9px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header ul li:nth-child(2) {
  margin-left: 10px;
}
.ui-multiselect-menu.ui-widget-content{
    padding: 3px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-circle-close{
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon{
    position: relative;
    top: 1px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-closethick, .ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-check{
    margin-right: 2px;
}
.ui-multiselect-menu.ui-widget-content {
  box-shadow: 0px 0px 5px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.3);
}
.ui-multiselect-checkboxes{
    overflow-y: auto;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Callout Box */
.nx-page .callout-box{
    background: #254EA2;
    padding: 30px;
    color: white;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
    margin-bottom: 35px;
}
.nx-page .callout-box h2{
    font-weight: 400;
    color: white;
    font-size: 16pt;
}
.nx-page .callout-box .btn{
    background: #FFD400;
    color: black;
}
.nx-page .callout-box ul{
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.nx-template{
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
    margin: 10px;
}

/* General html */
.nx-page h1, .nx-page h2{
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    color: #939598;
}

.nx-template .btn{
    background: #254EA2;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: white;
    font-size: 13pt;
    height: 50px;
    line-height: 23px;
}
.nx-template{
    color: #6d6f71;
    font-size: 13pt;
    line-height: 18pt;
}
.nx-template a{
    color: #6d6f71;
}

.nx-template a:hover{
    text-decoration: underline;
}

/* vidyard override */
.vidyard_tmask{
    position: fixed !important;
}

.vidyard_play_button a:hover {
  background-position: 0px 0px;
}
.vidyard_play_button a {
  position: absolute;
  margin: -42px 0 0 -26px;
  border-radius: 0px;
  background-position: 0px 0px;
  height: 85px;
  width: 72px;
  background-image: url(data:image/png;base64,);
}</cssitem><cssitem location="inline" name="mailico" cachelocation="false">.mail-icon{
    margin-right: 10px;
    margin-left: 10px;
}
.mail-icon:first-child{
    margin-left: 0px;
}</cssitem></css></resources></skuidpage>

<h3>SPONSOR & CO-MARKET OPPORTUNITIES</h3></br>
<p>Informatica offers a number of opportunities for partners to participate, sponsor, and co-market throughout the course of the year. Our events calendar consists of partner and end user activities.</p>
<p>To view upcoming events, please <a href="https://www.informatica.com/about-us/events.html" target="_blank">visit our corporate site</a>.</p>
</br>
<h3>ANNUAL INFORMATICA HOSTED EVENTS</h3></br>
<p>Annual Informatica-hosted events of particular interest to our partners include:</p>
<strong>Partner Summit/ Forum - Worldwide & Regional</strong></br>
<i>Worldwide Annual Partner Summit</i>
<p>This annual networking, enablement, and business development event is designed specifically to help boost your Informatica investment and generate increased sales opportunities. As an attending partner, your organization is listed in the Partner Profile booklet that is handed out to our global sales organization.</p>
<i>Regional Summits, Forums</i>
<p>These regionally based and focused events provide partners with the opportunity to hear from regional and global executives on our plans, products, and resources for partners.</p>
<strong>Informatica World</strong>
<p>This annual customer focused event offers education, training, and networking for our customers and partners. Learn more at
<a href="http://www.informaticaworld.com" target="_blank">www.informaticaworld.com</a>. Partners find value in sponsoring this event, for exposure to both the Informatica executive and sales teams, as well as end-user customers.</p>
<p>To discover more about sponsorship opportunities, contact your local partner marketing professional.</p></contents></template></components></panel><panel width="300"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>UPCOMING EVENTS</h2></br>

.nx-page .ui-widget, .nx-page body, .nx-page td {
    font-family: arial;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Page Titles */

.nx-pagetitle .ui-widget {
    font-family: Futura;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color:#939598;
}

/* Buttons */

.nx-actionbutton {
    float: left;
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    
}
.nx-actionselect {
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: #FFF;
    -webkit-border-radius: 0;
    -moz-border-radius: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: arial;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    padding-right: 10px;
    padding-left: 10px;
    padding-top:20px;
    padding-bottom:20px
}

.nx-actionbutton:hover {
    float: left;
    background: #FFD400;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
}
.nx-actionselect:hover {
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: #000;
    -webkit-border-radius: 0;
    -moz-border-radius: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: arial;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    padding-right: 10px;
    padding-left: 10px;
    padding-top:20px;
    padding-bottom:20px;
}

.nx-pagetitle .ui-widget .ui-button, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default {
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: white;
    -webkit-border-radius: 0;
    -moz-border-radius: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: arial;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    padding-right: 10px;
    padding-left: 10px;
    padding-top:20px;
    padding-bottom:20px
}

/* Tables */

table.nx-skootable-data th {
    background: #939598;
    height:45px;
    font-family: Futura;
    font-weight: 100;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody td, table.nx-skootable-data thead td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid white;
    height: 45px;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    background: #F0F0F0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    font-family: arial;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr:nth-child(odd) td {
    background-color:#F0F0F0
}

/* Field Editors */

.nx-basicfieldeditor-section-header {
    color: #939598;
    font-family:arial;
    font-size: 13pt;
    font-weight: 100;
}

.nx-basicfieldeditor-item .nx-field, .nx-basicfieldeditor-item .nx-basicfieldeditor-item-label {
    font-family:arial;
    font-size:13pt;
    color: #939598;
    font-weight:100
}
</cssitem></css><javascript/></resources></skuidpage>

.nx-page .ui-widget, body .nx-page, .nx-page td {
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Page Titles */

.nx-pagetitle-maintitle .ui-widget {
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Buttons */

.nx-actionbutton {
    float: left;
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    -webkit-border-radius: 3px;
    -moz-border-radius: 3px;
}

.ui-button, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default{
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: white;
    font-size: 12pt !important;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
}
.ui-button .ui-button-text{
    line-height: 41px;
}
.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-button-text{
    padding-left: 23px;
}

.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-icon{
    margin-top: -8px;
}

.ui-button.ui-state-hover, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default:hover{
    color: black;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary{
    color: #254EA2;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary.ui-state-hover{
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
    color: #254EA2;
    background: #eee;
}

.nx-actionselect {
    background: #254EA2;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: #FFF;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    line-height: 41px;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
    border-bottom: none;
}

.nx-actionselect.nx-conditiontoken:hover{
    background: #FFD400;
    color: black;
}

.nx-actionselect:hover, .nx-actionbutton:hover {
    color: #000;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.nx-actionselect.unavailable:hover, .nx-actionbutton.unavailable:hover {
    color: white;
    background: #ddd;
    cursor: default;
}

/* Dropdown */
.nx-actionselect-dropdown{
  background: none;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item {
  background: #254EA2;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #446AB8;
  color: white;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
  opacity: 1;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:first-child {
  border-top-right-radius: 3px;
  border-top-left-radius: 3px;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:last-child {
  border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom: none;
}


/* Tables */

table.nx-skootable-data {
    border-collapse:separate;
}

table.nx-skootable-data th {
    background: #939598;
    height:45px;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: lighter;
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    text-align:left;
    padding-left:10px;
    padding-right:10px;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody td, table.nx-skootable-data thead td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid white;
    height: 45px;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    background: #F0F0F0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

table.nx-skootable-data a {
    font-size: 13pt;
    color:#254EA2;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr td:nth-child(odd) {
    background-color:#F9F9F9
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr:nth-child(odd) td:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #F0F0F0;
}

table.nx-skootable-data .nx-skootable-order-icon{
    margin-top: 3px;
    background: url(data:image/png;base64,);
    width: 13px;
}

.nx-list-footer select {
    width:auto;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

.nx-list-footer {
    background:transparent;
}

.nx-list-footer .ui-button.ui-state-hover {
    background:#254EA2;
    color:white;
}
/* Table Search */

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox {
  width: 180px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  border: 1px solid #aaa;
  margin: 0 0 7px;
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
  line-height: 41px;
  height: 50px;
  background: #f5f5f5;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:disabled {
    background: #ddd;
    opacity: .6;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox::-webkit-input-placeholder {
   font-size: 12pt;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-moz-placeholder { /* Firefox 18- */
   font-size: 12pt; 
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox::-moz-placeholder {  /* Firefox 19+ */
   font-size: 12pt;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-ms-input-placeholder {  
   font-size: 12pt;
}

/* Field Editors */

.nx-basicfieldeditor-section-header {
  padding: 8px;
  border-bottom: none;
  font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16pt;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: #939598;
}

/* Tabs */
.ui-tabs{
    background: none;
}
.ui-tabs-nav{
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
}
.nx-lefttabs>.ui-tabs-nav li a{
    font-size: 12pt;    
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav .ui-tabs-anchor{
    width: 100%;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active, .ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active.ui-state-hover{
    background: #FFD400;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active a, .ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active.ui-state-hover a{
    color: black;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li{
    background: #254EA2;
    border-right:none;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-state-hover{
    background: #2A58B8;
}

.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:first-child{
    border-top-left-radius: 3px;
    border-top-right-radius: 3px;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:last-child{
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
}
.new-registration.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:nth-last-child(2){
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
}
/* Forms */
.nx-basicfieldeditor-item-label.nx-layout-above{
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #939598;
    line-height: 22pt;
    font-weight: 400;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-columngroup {
    background: none;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor{
    background: none;
    padding: 10px;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-section{
    background: none;
    margin: 10px;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-item{
    border-bottom: none;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor .nx-field input:not([type]){
    height: 25px;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}
.nx-editor .nx-basicfieldeditor-item select{
    max-width: none;
    height: 26px;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}
.nx-field input, .nx-field textarea, .nx-field select{
    background: white;
    border-color: #ddd;
    border-radius: 3px;
}

/* Wizard */
.nx-wizard .nx-editor-header-title{
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Multiselect */
.ui-multiselect-checkboxes label input{
    display: inline-block;
    position: relative;
    top: 3px;
}

button.ui-multiselect.ui-widget.ui-state-default {
  background: #254EA2;
  color: white;
  border-radius: 3px;
  border: none;
  min-height: 50px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  line-height: 41px;
}

button.ui-multiselect.ui-state-default:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
}

.ui-multiselect-header.ui-widget-header{
    background: #254EA2;
    font-size: 13pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    border: none;
    padding: 8px 3px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header ul li:nth-child(1) {
  margin-left: 9px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header ul li:nth-child(2) {
  margin-left: 10px;
}
.ui-multiselect-menu.ui-widget-content{
    padding: 3px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-circle-close{
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon{
    position: relative;
    top: 1px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-closethick, .ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-check{
    margin-right: 2px;
}
.ui-multiselect-menu.ui-widget-content {
  box-shadow: 0px 0px 5px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.3);
}
.ui-multiselect-checkboxes{
    overflow-y: auto;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Callout Box */
.nx-page .callout-box{
    background: #254EA2;
    padding: 30px;
    color: white;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
    margin-bottom: 35px;
}
.nx-page .callout-box h2{
    font-weight: 400;
    color: white;
    font-size: 16pt;
}
.nx-page .callout-box .btn{
    background: #FFD400;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: black;
    font-size: 13pt;
    height: 50px;
    line-height: 23px;
}
.nx-page .callout-box ul{
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.nx-template{
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

/* General html */
.nx-page h1, .nx-page h2{
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
}

/* vidyard override */
.vidyard_tmask{
    position: fixed !important;
}

.vidyard_play_button a:hover {
  background-position: 0px 0px;
}
.vidyard_play_button a {
  position: absolute;
  margin: -42px 0 0 -26px;
  border-radius: 0px;
  background-position: 0px 0px;
  height: 85px;
  width: 72px;
  background-image: url(data:image/png;base64,);
}</cssitem></css></resources></skuidpage>

Name: Products/Product-Request-Center
skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true" tabtooverride="Product_Request__c" theme="Modern"><models><model id="ProductRequest" limit="100" query="true" createrowifnonefound="false" sobject="Product_Request__c"><fields><field id="Name"/><field id="CreatedDate"/><field id="Status__c"/><field id="Customer_First_Name__c"/><field id="Customer_Last_Name__c"/><field id="OwnerId"/><field id="Owner.Name"/><field id="How_will_this_software_be_used__c"/></fields><conditions/><actions/></model></models><components><template multiple="true" model="ProductRequest" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>PRODUCT REQUEST CENTER</h2>
<p>As an Informatica partner, you may request software for internal enablement and demonstration purposes. Submit a new product request if you need to download a new product, or get a new license key for a product you have previously requested.</p>

<p>After you submit a request, our fulfillment team will get in touch with you in three to five business days regarding your request status. </p>

<p>Informatica provides license keys for six-month access for most products. Access to cloud products starts at 30 days, with the ability to extend the time period.</p>

<a class="btn" href="New_Product_Request">New Product Request</a></br></br>
<a class="btn" href="Existing_Product_Requests">Existing Product Requests</a></contents></template></components><resources><labels/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url="">
@font-face {
    font-family: FuturaPTB;
    src: url(/resource/PARC_fonts/FuturaStd-Book.otf);
}

@font-face {
    font-family: ArialPARC;
    src: url(/resource/PARC_fonts/Arial.ttf);
}

/* General Styling */

.nx-page .ui-widget, body .nx-page, .nx-page td {
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Page Titles */

.nx-pagetitle-maintitle .ui-widget {
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Buttons */

.nx-actionbutton {
    float: left;
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    -webkit-border-radius: 3px;
    -moz-border-radius: 3px;
}

.ui-button, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default{
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: white;
    font-size: 12pt !important;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
}
.ui-button .ui-button-text{
    line-height: 41px;
}
.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-button-text{
    padding-left: 23px;
}

.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-icon{
    margin-top: -8px;
}

.ui-button.ui-state-hover, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default:hover{
    color: black;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary{
    color: #254EA2;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary.ui-state-hover{
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
    color: #254EA2;
    background: #eee;
}

.nx-actionselect {
    background: #254EA2;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: #FFF;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    line-height: 41px;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
    border-bottom: none;
}

.nx-actionselect.nx-conditiontoken:hover{
    background: #FFD400;
    color: black;
}

.nx-actionselect:hover, .nx-actionbutton:hover {
    color: #000;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.nx-actionselect.unavailable:hover, .nx-actionbutton.unavailable:hover {
    color: white;
    background: #ddd;
    cursor: default;
}

/* Dropdown */
.nx-actionselect-dropdown{
  background: none;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item {
  background: #254EA2;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #446AB8;
  color: white;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
  opacity: 1;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:first-child {
  border-top-right-radius: 3px;
  border-top-left-radius: 3px;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:last-child {
  border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom: none;
}


/* Tables */

table.nx-skootable-data {
    border-collapse:separate;
}

table.nx-skootable-data th {
    background: #939598;
    height:45px;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: lighter;
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    text-align:left;
    padding-left:10px;
    padding-right:10px;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody td, table.nx-skootable-data thead td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid white;
    height: 45px;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    background: #F0F0F0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

table.nx-skootable-data a {
    font-size: 13pt;
    color:#254EA2;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr td:nth-child(odd) {
    background-color:#F9F9F9
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr:nth-child(odd) td:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #F0F0F0;
}

table.nx-skootable-data .nx-skootable-order-icon{
    margin-top: 3px;
    background: url(data:image/png;base64,);
    width: 13px;
}

.nx-list-footer select {
    width:auto;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

.nx-list-footer {
    background:transparent;
}

.nx-list-footer, .nx-list-footer .nx-list-loadmore{
    font-size: 12pt;
}
.nx-list-footer .ui-button{
    height: auto;
}
.nx-list-footer .ui-button.ui-state-hover {
    background:#254EA2;
    color:white;
}
.nx-list-footer .nx-list-footer-center {
  margin: 0 11px;
}
/* Table Search */

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox {
  width: 180px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  border: 1px solid #aaa;
  margin: 0 0 7px;
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
  line-height: 41px;
  height: 50px;
  background: #f5f5f5;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:disabled {
    background: #ddd;
    opacity: .6;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox::-webkit-input-placeholder {
   font-size: 12pt;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-moz-placeholder { /* Firefox 18- */
   font-size: 12pt; 
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox::-moz-placeholder {  /* Firefox 19+ */
   font-size: 12pt;
}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-ms-input-placeholder {  
   font-size: 12pt;
}

/* Field Editors */

.nx-basicfieldeditor-section-header {
  padding: 8px;
  border-bottom: none;
  font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16pt;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: #939598;
}

/* Tabs */
.ui-tabs{
    background: none;
}
.ui-tabs-nav{
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
}
.nx-lefttabs>.ui-tabs-nav li a{
    font-size: 12pt;    
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav .ui-tabs-anchor{
    width: 100%;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active, .ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active.ui-state-hover{
    background: #FFD400;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active a, .ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-tabs-active.ui-state-hover a{
    color: black;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li{
    background: #254EA2;
    border-right:none;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li.ui-state-hover{
    background: #2A58B8;
}

.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:first-child{
    border-top-left-radius: 3px;
    border-top-right-radius: 3px;
}
.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:last-child{
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
}
.new-registration.ui-tabs .ui-tabs-nav li:nth-last-child(2){
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
}
/* Forms */
.nx-basicfieldeditor-item-label.nx-layout-above{
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #939598;
    line-height: 22pt;
    font-weight: 400;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-columngroup {
    background: none;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor{
    background: none;
    padding: 10px;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-section{
    background: none;
    margin: 10px;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor-item{
    border-bottom: none;
}
.nx-basicfieldeditor .nx-field input:not([type]){
    height: 25px;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}
.nx-editor .nx-basicfieldeditor-item select{
    max-width: none;
    height: 26px;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}
.nx-field input, .nx-field textarea, .nx-field select{
    background: white;
    border-color: #ddd;
    border-radius: 3px;
}

/* Wizard */
.nx-wizard .nx-editor-header-title{
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Multiselect */
.ui-multiselect-checkboxes label input{
    display: inline-block;
    position: relative;
    top: 3px;
}

button.ui-multiselect.ui-widget.ui-state-default {
  background: #254EA2;
  color: white;
  border-radius: 3px;
  border: none;
  min-height: 50px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  line-height: 41px;
}

button.ui-multiselect.ui-state-default:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
}

.ui-multiselect-header.ui-widget-header{
    background: #254EA2;
    font-size: 13pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    border: none;
    padding: 8px 3px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header ul li:nth-child(1) {
  margin-left: 9px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header ul li:nth-child(2) {
  margin-left: 10px;
}
.ui-multiselect-menu.ui-widget-content{
    padding: 3px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-circle-close{
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon{
    position: relative;
    top: 1px;
}
.ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-closethick, .ui-multiselect-header .ui-icon-check{
    margin-right: 2px;
}
.ui-multiselect-menu.ui-widget-content {
  box-shadow: 0px 0px 5px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.3);
}
.ui-multiselect-checkboxes{
    overflow-y: auto;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Callout Box */
.nx-page .callout-box{
    background: #254EA2;
    padding: 30px;
    color: white;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
    margin-bottom: 35px;
}
.nx-page .callout-box h2{
    font-weight: 400;
    color: white;
    font-size: 16pt;
}
.nx-page .callout-box .btn{
    background: #FFD400;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: black;
    font-size: 13pt;
    height: 50px;
    line-height: 23px;
}
.nx-page .callout-box ul{
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.nx-template{
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

/* General html */
.nx-page h1, .nx-page h2{
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
}
</cssitem></css><javascript/></resources></skuidpage>

<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>PRODUCT SUPPORT</h2>
<p>All INFORM Partners have access to MySupport, our customer and partner support center. The number of users that may register for MySupport depends on your partner level. If you have questions about who in your organization has been designated as MySupport administrators, please <a href="Contact_Us">contact us</a>.</p> 
<p>MySupport can be used to request technical support as well as access technical documentation on Informatica products. Resources available to you include:</p>
<ul><li><strong>How-to Library</strong> - articles and tutorials to help guide you through specific tasks</li>
<li><strong>Product Documentation</strong> - developer guides, release notes, user manuals</li>
<li><strong>Debugging Tools</strong> - free tools to help debug your environment faster</li>
<li><strong>Troubleshooting Wizards</strong> - to find quick solutions to problems</li>
<li><strong>Support TV</strong> - self help videos addressing common questions</li>
</ul></br>
<p>Please note that MySupport is not part of Informatica Passport, so you will need a separate username and password to access the system.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://mysupport.informatica.com/login/login.html" target="_blank">Access MySupport</a></contents></template></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="false">

<h3>Turn Prospects into Customers, Opportunities into Sales</h3>
<p>The INFORM Program enables you to leverage our expertise and your salesforce by providing you with the information, resources and programs to identify and close new business opportunities. This section will empower your salesforce with:</p>
<ul><li>Information.  Relevant, topical materials and webinars on how to position and sell our products; five solution plays that exploit our advantages and differentiation; profile of our customers and industries. </li>
<li>Partner Opportunity Registration and Management System.  Access our opportunity registration and management system – register and manage a prospect through the sales process with this easy to use system.</li>  
<li>Incentives and Promotions.  Participate in targeted programs and promotions for your customers and sales organization.</li>
<li>Informatica Sales Contacts. Identify and engage with our field sales organization in prospecting and account development/planning efforts.  Where possible and appropriate, connect with our direct sales organization on specific accounts and opportunities.</li>
</ul></contents></template></components></panel><panel width="380px"><components><template multiple="true" model="Content" allowhtml="true"><contents><div class="callout-box">
<h2>NEED SALES SUPPORT?</h2>
<p>Working on an opportunity and need Informatica information? Reach out to our partner support team and get help!</p>

<strong>Informatica Opportunities are Everywhere – Register Them Today</strong></br>
<p>Our opportunity management system enables you to register and manage new business opportunities to close. The simple yet comprehensive system will provide your salesforce with the ability to track and move the opportunity through the sales cycle to close.</p>
<p>Informatica employs a proven methodology and process engineered for a successful close.  Here is a visual of the sales lifecycle with information and actions for every stage.</p>
<img src="">
<p>This opportunity lifecycle provides customer and partner actions and outcomes concluding with the completion of documentation to be submitted to the Sales Operations Group.</p>

<p>The purpose of using Opportunity Registration is to collaborate and secure your legitimacy to work on opportunities by recording your involvement. It allows you to formally register your involvement by automatically informing the Informatica team. The Informatica team will review the opportunity and then initiate the approval process. This ensures real time collaboration between you and the Informatica team. 
</p>

skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>RESOURCES</h2>
<p>INFORM partners have access a broad collection of resources to accelerate your understanding and application of our offerings to your target customers.</p>
<h2>PRESALES AND SALES TRAINING</h2>
<p>Informatica offers partners complimentary access to the curriculum our own salesforce and sales consultants take to gain competency in selling, demonstrating and helping present the benefits to customers of Informatica products. Similar to Informatica Sales Training but with more of a deep dive on products, this three-part sales training series covers the whole sales cycle from identify and qualify (available now), position and present (later in 2015), through close (later in 2015).</br></br>
<a class="btn" href="Presales_Sales_Competency">ACCESS TRAINING</a></p></br>
<h2>STRAIGHT SCOOPS</h2>
<p>In addition to sales presentations on our products (which include target customers, market opportunity, key Informatica differentiators, key selling messages and resources, etc.) we offer Straight Scoops – an expanding collection of webinars.
Straight Scoops are individual webinars that you can view anytime and anywhere.  The webinars are typically one hour in length and packed with relevant detail that will help you effectively position our products to your prospects.</p>
<p>Subjects include:</p>
<ul><li>Informatica Cloud Integration Solutions - Positioning, Use Cases, & Interoperability</li>
<li>Hortonworks Joint Offering for Hadoop: Putting Big Data into production quicker</li>
<li>MDM 10 - New Capabilities And Positioning</li></ul></br>
<a class="btn" href="Straight_Scoops">ACCESS STRAIGHT SCOOPS</a>
</p></contents></template></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url=""/></css></resources></skuidpage>

Name: Sales/Resources/Straight-Scoops
skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models><model id="NewModel" limit="20" query="true" createrowifnonefound="false" sobject="Vidyard_master_record__c"><fields><field id="Video_ID__c"/><field id="Name__c"/><field id="CreatedDate"/><field id="Description__c"/><field id="Video_link__c"/></fields><conditions/><actions/></model></models><components><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>STRAIGHT SCOOPS</h2></contents></template><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><div style="background-color: #BCBDBF; padding:4px;"><b>Beyond The Dots - Understanding Analyst Impact In Your Deals</b></div></contents></template><panelset type="custom" scroll=""><panels><panel width="300"><components><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><div align="left">
<script type="text/javascript" id="vidyard_embed_code_CnWjieCSxMOX6XNs34dDbQ" src="//play.vidyard.com/CnWjieCSxMOX6XNs34dDbQ.js?v=3.1&type=lightbox"></script><div class="outer_vidyard_wrapper"><div class="vidyard_wrapper" onclick="fn_vidyard_CnWjieCSxMOX6XNs34dDbQ();"><img alt="20141202 (SS) Beyond The Dots - Understanding Analyst Impact In Your Deals" src="//play.vidyard.com/CnWjieCSxMOX6XNs34dDbQ.jpg?" width="300" /><div class="vidyard_play_button"><a href="javascript:void(0);"></a></div></div></div>
</br><p>Date Published: 12/2/2014</br>
Video Length: 00:34</p></div></contents></template></components></panel><panel width="600"><components><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><p>Although Informatica is a leader in many Gartner Magic Quadrants and Forrester Waves, it’s not an automatic given that Gartner or Forrester will always recommend INFA to your prospects. According to Informatica’s win/loss data, 60% of our customers and prospects last year consulted industry analyst reports to create a short list. We see industry analysts such as Gartner and Forrester directly impact many of our larger deals. Customers pay thousands of dollars to these analyst firms to get IT advice and they often place more trust in these analysts than a vendor. Attend this Straight Scoop so you know how these analysts could positively or negatively impact your deals.</p>
<p>In this session you will learn to:</p>
<p><ul>
<li>Leverage analyst research to differentiate INFA positively from our competitors</li>
<li>Assess analyst impact in your deal so that you’re not surprised</li>
<li>Reposition any negative impact from analysts that may arise in your deal</li>
</ul></p>
</contents></template></components></panel></panels></panelset><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><div style="background-color: #BCBDBF; padding:4px;"><b>MDM 10 - New Capabilities And Positioning</b></div></contents></template><panelset type="custom" scroll=""><panels><panel width="300"><components><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><div align="left">
<script type="text/javascript" id="vidyard_embed_code_xquJPOt6fTayiNRKcNMUsQ" src="//play.vidyard.com/xquJPOt6fTayiNRKcNMUsQ.js?v=3.1&type=lightbox"></script><div class="outer_vidyard_wrapper"><div class="vidyard_wrapper" onclick="fn_vidyard_xquJPOt6fTayiNRKcNMUsQ();"><img alt="20141204 (TSS) - MDM v10 - Technical Capabilities, Features, & Functions" src="//play.vidyard.com/xquJPOt6fTayiNRKcNMUsQ.jpg?" width="300" /><div class="vidyard_play_button"><a href="javascript:void(0);"></a></div></div></div></br>
</br><p>Date Published: 11/18/2014</br>
Video Length: 01:03</p></div></contents></template></components></panel><panel width="600"><components><template multiple="true" model="NewModel" allowhtml="true"><contents><p>Informatica MDM 10 is the most important release to date—it is the first Informatica product to embed Vibe and it is the first instantiation of Informatica’s Intelligent Data Platform (IDP), embedding DI, DQ, and BPM within MDM. It introduces innovative capabilities aimed at leapfrogging the competition.</p>
<p>In this session you will learn about:</p>
<ul><li>Key product capabilities in Informatica Multidomain MDM 10</li>
<li>How to position the product and tie it to customer requirements</li>
<li>How it beats the competition – a competitive comparison</li>
<li>Changes to pricing and packaging</li>
<li>Where to go for more resources and support</li></ul></contents></template></components></panel></panels></panelset></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url=""/></css></resources></skuidpage>

Name: Sales/Selling-with-Informatica
skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>Selling Informatica Offerings</h2>
<p>Partners are integral to the success of our go to market efforts. Partners may have the opportunity to work with our sales and support organizations on managing and closing opportunities. We look forward to a highly collaborative engagement model with partners, particularly with Informatica's announcement and focus on the <a href="5_Plays">2015 Sales Plays</a>. Information on our field sales management can be found in the <a href="Sales_Contacts">sales contacts section</a>.</br>
<p style="text-align:center"><img src="http://i58.tinypic.com/sav7ue.jpg" width="650"> </p></br>
<p>Informatica has three sales motions in reaching its target customers:
<ol><li>Informatica sells via a direct sales force, responsible for managing the end to end sales process. Informatica is responsible for the transaction, and in many instances, the deployment. There may be opportunities for partners to assist in the deployment or fulfillment.</li>
<li>Informatica teams with a partner or partners to provide the customer with their desired solution. Informatica would be responsible for the sales transaction, while the partner can support deliverables in the sales process. Assisting the sale could include, among other things, business and technology assessments and briefings, solutioning and proof of concept activities.</li>
<li>Partners reselling Informatica are responsible for the end to end sales process and completing the sales transaction. Partners wishing to resell will need to sign the appropriate agreements with Informatica.</li>
</ol></p>
<p>Our go to market plans include all of these sales motions. Informatica will value and leverage partner capabilities for existing and new customer opportunities. The INFORM Program Guide will provide you with additional information on teaming and resell benefits.</p></contents></template></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url=""/></css></resources></skuidpage>

@font-face {

@font-face {

/* General Styling */

.nx-page .ui-widget, body .nx-page, .nx-page td {
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

/* Page Titles */

.nx-pagetitle-maintitle .ui-widget {
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 16pt;
    color: #6d6f71;
}

/* Buttons */

.nx-actionbutton {
    float: left;
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    -webkit-border-radius: 3px;
    -moz-border-radius: 3px;
}

.ui-button, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default{
    background: #254EA2;
    margin: 0 6px 5px 0;
    border-radius:3px;
    color: white;
    font-size: 12pt !important;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
}
.ui-button .ui-button-text{
    line-height: 41px;
}
.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-button-text{
    padding-left: 23px;
}

.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-icon{
    margin-top: -8px;
}

.ui-button.ui-state-hover, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default:hover{
    color: black;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary{
    color: #254EA2;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary.ui-state-hover{
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #254EA2 inset;
    border-color: #254EA2;
    color: #254EA2;
    background: #eee;
}

.nx-actionselect {
    background: #254EA2;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;
    color: #FFF;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 12pt;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    margin: 0 4px 7px 0;
    border:none;
    box-shadow:none;
    line-height: 41px;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 0px 10px;
    border-bottom: none;
}

.nx-actionselect.nx-conditiontoken:hover{
    background: #FFD400;
    color: black;
}

.nx-actionselect:hover, .nx-actionbutton:hover {
    color: #000;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.nx-actionselect.unavailable:hover, .nx-actionbutton.unavailable:hover {
    color: white;
    background: #ddd;
    cursor: default;
}

/* Dropdown */
.nx-actionselect-dropdown{
  background: none;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item {
  background: #254EA2;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #446AB8;
  color: white;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:hover {
  background: #FFD400;
  color: black;
  opacity: 1;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:first-child {
  border-top-right-radius: 3px;
  border-top-left-radius: 3px;
}

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:last-child {
  border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
  border-bottom: none;
}


/* Tables */

table.nx-skootable-data {
    border-collapse:separate;
}

table.nx-skootable-data th {
    background: #939598;
    height:45px;
    font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
    font-weight: lighter;
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    text-align:left;
    padding-left:10px;
    padding-right:10px;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody td, table.nx-skootable-data thead td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid white;
    height: 45px;
    border-right: 1px solid white;
    background: #F0F0F0;
    vertical-align: middle;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
}

table.nx-skootable-data a {
    font-size: 13pt;
    color:#254EA2;
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr td:nth-child(odd) {
    background-color:#F9F9F9
}

table.nx-skootable-data tbody tr:nth-child(odd) td:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #F0F0F0;
}

table.nx-skootable-data .nx-skootable-order-icon{
    margin-top: 3px;
    background: url(data:image/png;base64,);
    width: 13px;
}
table .nx-skootable-order-number{
    display: none !important;
}

.nx-list-footer select {
    width:auto;
    font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;
}

.nx-list-footer {
    background:transparent;
}

.nx-list-footer .ui-button.ui-state-hover {
    background:#254EA2;
    color:white;

/* Table Search */

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox {
  width: 180px;
  font-size: 12pt;
  border: 1px solid #aaa;
  margin: 0 0 7px;
  font-family: ArialPARC, sans-serif;

  height: 50px;
  background: #f5f5f5;

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-moz-placeholder { /* Firefox 18- */

}

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox:-ms-input-placeholder {

/* Field Editors */

.nx-basicfieldeditor-section-header {
  padding: 8px;
  border-bottom: none;
  font-family: FuturaPTB, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16pt;
  font-weight: 400;

/* Tabs */

<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><panelset type="vertical"><panels><panel width="100%"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>CREDENTIALS FOR PARTNERS</h2>
<p>Informatica offers partner employees two types of credentials: Certification and Presales & Sales Competency. Certification covers competency around Informatica products, whereas Presales & Sales Competency focuses on selling these products. Courseware is available for both  on INFORM Learning, our learning management system.</p><p>The table below is a guide to understanding the difference between the two credentials: </br>
<table style="background-color: #999; border-collapse: separate; border-spacing: 1pt;" width="100%" cellpadding="10">
    <tbody>
        <tr style="color: #FFF; background-color: #1d1d1d;">
            <td width="150px;">
            <p><strong><font color="#FFFFFF">Credential</font></strong></p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p><strong><font color="#FFFFFF">Audience</font></strong></p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p><strong><font color="#FFFFFF">Objective</font></strong></p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p><strong><font color="#FFFFFF">Content</font></strong></p>
            </td>
	    <td>
            <p><strong><font color="#FFFFFF">Pricing</font></strong></p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #FFF;">
            <td style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p><strong><a href="Partner_Certification">Informatica Certification</a></strong></br></p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p>Presales, Professional Services, and Consultants</p>
            </td>
            <td style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p>Specific packages for developing and/ or administering Informatica offerings.</p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p><ul><li>Technical features and functions</li><li>Product usage and demos</li></p>
            </td>
	     <td style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p>Aggressively priced for INFORM Partners</p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #FFF">
             <td style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p><strong><a href="Presales_Sales_Competency">Presales & Sales Competency</a></strong></br></p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p>Presales and Sales</p>
            </td>
             <td style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p>Ability to position, promote, and sell Informatica offerings.</p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p><ul><li>Soft skills and technical selling</li><li>Solution messaging</li><li>Technical product positioning and differentiator</li></ul></p>
            </td>
	     <td style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p>No charge for INFORM Partners</p>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table></contents></template></components></panel></panels></panelset></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url=""/></css></resources></skuidpage>

Name: Training/Credentials/Certification
skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true" theme="Modern"><models/><components><panelset type="vertical"><panels><panel width="225"><components><template multiple="true" model="" allowhtml="true" cssclass=""><contents><h2>CERTIFICATION</h2>
<p>Informatica requires all INFORM Partners to have a number of their professionals certified on the Informatica products they intend to promote. Certification requirements vary depending on partner level  - <a href="/apex/training-requirements">click here for requirements</a>.</p>
<p>Courseware in any of the certification packages is available 24x7, which enables the employee to take it at any time, based on their schedule. Virtual training reduces the time and expense incurred when away from the office. The aggressive pricing for these packages will reduce your quarterly and annual training expenses. Achieving certification on PowerCenter, MDM, or any of the other offered packages demonstrates competency within the partner practice - valued by your target customers.</p>

<p> The Certify Now offers certification at an aggressive price, to enable partners to have more of their staff certified on Informatica offerings. Every package includes the courseware, lab time, and the exam for achieving certification. We currently offer seven certifications, with more under development and planned for in the coming months.</p></contents></template></components></panel><panel><components><panelset type="vertical"><panels><panel width="225"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>LIST OF CERTIFICATION PACKAGES:</h2></br></contents></template><tabset rememberlastusertab="true" defertabrendering="true" renderas="lefttabs" cssclass=""><tabs><tab name="PowerCenter Developer"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3>
<p><b>PowerCenter 9.x: Developer, Level 1 </b></br> 
Students are introduced to Informatica PowerCenter 9.x through a series of 16 onDemand modules and 40 hours of lab exercises. Develop cleansing, formatting, sorting, and aggregating procedures. This course will cover various types of lookups, such as cached, persistent, and multiple row returns.</p>
<p><b>PowerCenter 9.x: Developer, Level 2</b></br>
Through a series of 13 onDemand modules and 20 hours of labs, review advanced topics to compliment and extend the Level 1 class. Advanced topics include:
<ul><li>High Availability</li>
<li>Pipeline Look-up & Dynamic Look-up Expressions</li>
<li>SQL Transformation & Transaction Control Transformations</li></li></ul>
</p><a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=2759cbf4-d1fe-4bbb-bfbd-68a48ad7521a#t=1" target="_blank">REGISTER</a>
</contents></template></components><renderconditions logictype="and"/></tab><tab name=" PowerCenter Administrator" loadlazypanels="true"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3>
<p><b>PowerCenter 9.x: Administration </b></br> 
In this course, students will learn to administer the PowerCenter platform. The course is intended for either PowerCenter administrators with one year or more of professional experience, or those who have attended previous Informatica Level 1 Developer training classes.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=38480db9-0505-47d6-90e6-44d594b40580" target="_blank">REGISTER</a>

</contents></template></components></tab><tab name=" Data Quality Developer" loadlazypanels="true"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3>
<p><b>Data Quality 9.x: Developer</b></br> 
Informatica Developer is a thick client workbench tool that developers can use to profile, cleanse, standardize, de-duplicate, and consolidate data in the enterprise.</p>
<p>This is an introductory course to the Data Quality 9.x Developer Tool, providing users with a high level overview of the Data Quality Process, setting a foundation for the processes that follow. This course is taught through a series of 16 onDemand modules and 40 hours of lab</p>
<p><b>Data Quality 9.x: Analyst</b></br> 
Informatica Analyst is a web-based application client that analysts can use to analyze, profile, and score data in an enterprise. Students are introduced to the Data Quality 9.x Analyst tool through a series of 5 onDemand modules and 20 hours of lab exercises.</p>
<p><b>Data Quality 9.x: Developer, Level 2 onDemand</b></br> 
A course designed for Developers who have previously completed the Informatica Data Quality Level 1 course and are more experienced. This is a continuation of the Level 1 course, focusing in more detail topics such as building Classifier and NER models, Parsing, Matching, AV settings, Human Tasks, and Workflows. Additional topics include Association, Parameters, and DQ for Excel.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=9d2711dd-6e16-4bf4-b41a-a3c34ebae211#t=1" target="_blank">REGISTER</a></contents></template></components></tab><tab name="MDM Hub Developer" loadlazypanels="true"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3><p><b>MDM 9.x Multidomain Edition: Configuration</b></br> 
This course provides students with the knowledge and skills necessary to configure a data model and business rules in Informatica MDM Multidomain Edition (MDM Hub) for a given data model and business rules design. The course provides extensive hands-on labs and exercises to allow students to gain confidence in the use of the MDM console.</p>
<p><b>MDM 9.x: Configuring Hierarchy Manager</b></br> 
This one-day course provides the configuration specialist with the skills to configure entity objects, entity types, hierarchies, relationship base objects, relationship types, and profiles on the Siperian Hierarchy Manager.</p>
<p><b>MDM Data Director 9.x: Configuration</b></br> 
This course provides configuration specialists with the essential concepts to understand what goes into a BDD implementation, introducing them to the fundamental capabilities of the BDD user interface. It also teaches them how to build BDD applications and customize the BDD interface.</p>
<p><b>MDM Service Integration Framework API</b></br> 
This course will prepare the Master Data Management developers to work with Informatica Service Integration Framework based on the Informatica MDM 9.x release. Developers will learn critical information starting with high-level architecture and concepts down to the technical-level details to deploy the technology effectively.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=924da8b7-3d56-4042-b12a-fac401817702#t=1" target="_blank">REGISTER</a></contents></template></components></tab><tab name="MDM Administrator" loadlazypanels="true"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3>

<p><b>MDM 9.x Multidomain Edition: Configuration</b></br> 
This course provides students with the knowledge and skills necessary to configure a data model and business rules in Informatica MDM Multidomain Edition (MDM Hub) for a given data model and business rules design. The course provides extensive hands-on labs and exercises to allow students to gain confidence in the use of the MDM console.</p>
<p><b>MDM: Administration</b></br> 
This eLearning overview provides an introduction and description to the core components of Informatica Master Data Management (MDM).</p>
<p><b>MDM 9.x: Multidomain Edition, Administration</b></br> 
In this course, attendees will learn the skills needed administer the MDM Multidomain Edition (MDM Hub). Hands-on labs include performing MDM Hub administration, maintenance, and management tasks.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=0c7ea754-d75b-4678-8a38-96b5e895e970#t=1" target="_blank">REGISTER</a></contents></template></components></tab><tab name="Test Data Management" loadlazypanels="true"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3>

<p><b>PowerCenter 9.x: Developer, Level 1</b></br> 
Students are introduced to Informatica PowerCenter 9.x through a series of 16 onDemand modules and 40 hours of lab exercises. Develop cleansing, formatting, sorting, and aggregating procedures. This course will cover various types of lookups, such as cached, persistent, and multiple row returns.</p>
<p><b>ILM Test Data Management - Data Subset and Data Masking</b></br> 
This onDemand class will prepare you to make the best use of Informatica ILM Test Data Management in your environment. The entire process from importing metadata, defining constrains, and deploying data subset and data masking solutions is described and followed with labs.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=45495238-ae11-4fc0-94f1-86142017e7fd#t=1" target="_blank">REGISTER</a></contents></template></components></tab><tab name="Data Archive" loadlazypanels="true"><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h3>Certification Package Description:</h3>
<p><b>ILM Data Archive 6.x: Live Archiving Base</b></br> 
This course prepares students to make the best use of Informatica's ILM Data Archive product in the environment. Students will perform administration activities on the ILM Application Server and File Archive Server. Through a series of onDemand modules as well as hands-on lab exercises, this course offers deep insight into ILM Data Archive product features, components, and achitecture.</p>
<p><b>ILM Data Archive 6.x: Application Retirement</b></br> 
Students are taught to perform administration activities on ILM and IDV servers. Students will understand the security features of the product and create and manage functionalities.</p>
<a class="btn" href="https://informatica.csod.com/lms/LoDetails/DetailsLo.aspx?loid=80281a7e-93f1-4342-a81b-6856d1e0a55b#t=1" target="_blank">REGISTER</a></contents></template></components></tab></tabs></tabset></components></panel><panel><components/></panel></panels></panelset></components></panel></panels></panelset></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url="">
@font-face {

.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-button-text{

.ui-button-text-icon-primary .ui-icon{

}

.ui-button.ui-state-hover, .ui-widget-content .ui-button.ui-state-default:hover{
    color: black;
    background: #FFD400;
}

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary{

.ui-button.nx-button-secondary.ui-state-hover{

.nx-actionselect {
    background: #254EA2;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    position: relative;

    border-radius: 3px;

    font-size: 12pt;

.nx-actionselect-dropdown>.nx-actionselect-dropdown-item:last-child {

/* Tables */

table.nx-skootable-data {
    border-collapse:separate;
}

table.nx-skootable-data .nx-skootable-order-icon{

.nx-list-footer select {

}

.nx-list-footer {

/* Table Search */

.nx-editor-header input.searchbox {

.ui-tabs-nav{

}
.nx-lefttabs>.ui-tabs-nav, .nx-righttabs>.ui-tabs-nav{

<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><panelset type="standard" scroll=""><panels><panel><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>PRESALES & SALES COMPETENCY TRAINING</h2> 
<p>Informatica strongly recommends that all partner presales and sales employees have the practical knowledge to sell Informatica solutions. We have created courseware that will improve your ability to identify, qualify, and close on sales opportunities.</p>
<p>Partner presales and sales personnel can quickly achieve competency on one or more Informatica technologies. Our courseware is a tiered process beginning with Bronze (currently designated as Accreditation) followed by future Silver and Gold training. Available today is the set of Bronze training, with future releases planned on Silver and Gold courseware.</p>
<p>The entire set of courseware is provided at no charge to INFORM Partners.</p>
<p>Specific courseware for presales and sales can be accessed via these links:</p>
<a class="btn" href="Presales_Training">Presales</a></br></br>
<a class="btn" href="Sales_Training">Sales</a></contents></template></components></panel></panels></panelset></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="true" url=""/></css></resources></skuidpage>

            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #FFF">
             <td>
            <p><strong>Informatica Certified Packages for Partners</strong></br>Offered on (7) Informatica Product Solutions, Each Informatica Certified Package Contains All the Training Courses Required Plus the Corresponding Exam for an Individual to Become Certified as a Specialist on an Informatica Product Solution.</p>
            </td>
            <td>
            <p>Special Partner Savings Via the Certify Now Initiative</p>

        <tr style="background:  #bcbdc0;">
            <td colspan="2" style="background: #bcbdc0;">
            <p><strong>Informatica Cloud Academy</a></br></p>
            </td>

Name: Training/Program/Register
skuid__Layout__c:
<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><template multiple="false" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>REGISTER FOR TRAINING</h2></br>
<p>As an Informatica partner, you may register for on demand and instructor led training through INFORM Learning, our learning management system, as well as on demand training through Cloud Academy.</br></p></br>
<h2>LAST MINUTE SEAT REQUESTS</h2></br>
<p>The Complimentary Seat program offers our Partners the opportunity to request a last minute seat in any Pubic or Virtual course at no cost, based on availability.</p>
<p><strong>Program Guidelines</strong></p>
<p>Last Minute seats are complimentary to INFORM partners and are available on a first come, first serve basis.</p>
<ul><li>Request for a Complimentary Seat may be submitted 3 business days prior to course start date, no sooner.</li>
<li>It will be the responsibility of the Partner to register for any future class. Informatica University will not move the partner into other courses if there are no available seats.</li>
<li>Registration may be requested only in the geographical area of your Alliance agreement.</li>
<li>Informatica reserves the right to be flexible on complimentary seats due to customer demand.</li></ul></br>
<p><strong>Cancellation Policy</strong></p>
<p>To maximize the effectiveness of the Complimentary Seat program, the following cancellation policies apply:</p>
<ul><li>A no show fee of $100 a day for the length of the course will be charged should a partner not attend the course.</li>
<li>Substitutions are allowed within Partner Company and should be made at least 1 business day prior to course start date by contacting Informatica University.</li></ul></br>
<p><strong>Submit a Request for a Last Minute Seat</strong></p>
<p>Please use our <a href="Contact_Us">Contact Us form</a> to fill in your Contact Name, Company Name, Corporate Email Address, and Phone Number. Also include:</p>
<ul><li>Subject Line: Last Minute Seat Request</lI>
<li>What type of assistance do you need: Informatica University Question</li>
<li>Please describe in detail: Course ID, Course Name, Course Location, and Mailing address</li></ul></br>
<p>After you submit your request, Informatica University’s Training Registrar will notify you on whether you are confirmed or not for the course within 24 hours.</p></contents></template></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="MasterCSS" cachelocation="false"/></css></resources></skuidpage>

<skuidpage unsavedchangeswarning="yes" showsidebar="true" showheader="true"><models/><components><template multiple="true" model="" allowhtml="true"><contents><h2>TRAINING SYSTEMS</h2>
<p>We offer courseware through two training systems - INFORM Learning and Cloud Academy. Learn what is available to you as a partner on both of these learning centers:</p>
<strong>INFORM LEARNING</strong>
<p><a href="" target="_blank">INFORM Learning</a> is a partner exclusive resource that houses both Informatica University courseware, as well as sales & presales enablement classes.</p>
<strong>CLOUD ACADEMY</strong>
<p><a href="http://cloudacademy.informatica.com/" target="_blank">Cloud Academy</a> provides complimentary access to partners on all courseware. If you have not previously accessed the site, you will need to set up a new account - <a href="http://cloudacademy.informatica.com/login/index.php" target="_blank">click here</a> to register.</p></contents></template></components><resources><labels/><javascript/><css><cssitem location="staticresource" name="newcss" cachelocation="false"/></css></resources></skuidpage>
